Package core.exceptions

Package with all the exceptions for the API generated by Pitch Developer Studio.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    HlaAttributeAlreadyOwnedException
    Exception thrown if the federate tries to cancel acquire ownership of an attribute is has already received ownership of.
    HlaAttributeNotOwnedException
    Exception thrown if the attribute failed to be updated due to lacking ownership, or when trying to release an unowned attribute.
    HlaBaseException
    Base class for all checked exceptions.
    HlaBaseRuntimeException
    Base class for all unchecked, runtime, exception.
    HlaConnectException
    Exception thrown if the connection to the RTI failed.
    HlaDecodeException
    Exception thrown if the attribute or parameter could not be encoded or decoded.
    HlaFederateNotAcquiringAttributeException
    Exception thrown if the federate tries to cancel acquire ownership of an attribute it is not currently trying to acquire ownership of
    HlaFederateOwnsAttributeException
    Exception thrown if attempting to acquire an already owned attribute, or if ownership acquisitions are pending or if attributes are owned and this not handled by the resign action when disconnecting.
    HlaFomException
    Exception thrown if the current FOM does not match the FOM used to for code generation.
    HlaIllegalInstanceNameException
    Exception thrown if the requested HLA instance name is illegal.
    HlaIncompatibleHlaVersionException
    Exception thrown if the currently used HLA version can't support this method
    HlaInstanceNameInUseException
    Exception thrown if the requested HLA instance name is already in use.
    HlaInternalException
    Exception thrown if an internal error occurred.
    HlaInTimeAdvancingStateException
    Exception thrown if the operation can not be performed in the time advancing state.
    HlaInvalidInterestException
    Exception thrown if the interest is not valid.
    HlaInvalidLicenseException
    Exception thrown if the license is not valid.
    HlaInvalidLogicalTimeException
    Exception thrown if the logical time is invalid or can not be used.
    HlaNormalizerException
    Exception thrown if the normalizer is not set, or could not be set correctly.
    HlaNotConnectedException
    Exception thrown if not connected to the RTI and joined to the federation when performing an operation that require that.
    HlaObjectInstanceIsRemovedException
    Exception thrown if the object instance has been removed.
    HlaRestoreFederateException
    Exception thrown if a request to initiate a federate restore failed
    HlaRestoreInProgressException
    Exception thrown if any message is sent while a federation restore is in progress
    HlaRtiException
    Exception thrown if the RTI operation failed, for example RTI internal error.
    HlaSaveFederateException
    Exception thrown if a request to initiate a federate save failed
    HlaSaveInProgressException
    Exception thrown if any message is sent while a federation save is in progress
    HlaUpdaterReusedException
    Exception thrown if an updater is reused.
    HlaValueNotSetException
    Exception thrown if the attribute has no value.
